1. Proca Formulation Lagrangian density: L=−14FμνFμν+12mX2XμXμ−αXμJμ L=−41​Fμν​Fμν+21​mX2​Xμ​Xμ−αXμ​Jμ with Fμν=∂μXν−∂νXμFμν​=∂μ​Xν​−∂ν​Xμ​. Field equations: ∂νFνμ+mX2Xμ=αJμ ∂ν​Fνμ+mX2​Xμ=αJμ 2. Energy-Momentum Tensor from LL Using Tμν=−2∂L∂gμν+gμνLTμν=−2∂gμν​∂L​+gμνL: Tμν=FμαF αν−14gμνFαβFαβ+mX2(XμXν−12gμνXαXα)−αJ(μXν)+αgμνXαJα Tμν=FμαF αν​−41​gμνFαβ​Fαβ+mX2​(XμXν−21​gμνXα​Xα)−αJ(μXν)+αgμνXα​Jα 3. Verify Conservation ∂μTμν=0∂μ​Tμν=0 Compute divergence: ∂μTμν=(∂μFμα)F αν+Fμα∂μF αν−12Fαβ∂νFαβ+mX2(Xμ∂μXν+Xν∂μXμ−12Xα∂νXα)−α∂μ(J(μXν))+α∂ν(XαJα) ∂μ​Tμν=(∂μ​Fμα)F αν​+Fμα∂μ​F αν​−21​Fαβ​∂νFαβ+mX2​(Xμ∂μ​Xν+Xν∂μ​Xμ−21​Xα​∂νXα)−α∂μ​(J(μXν))+α∂ν(Xα​Jα) Using field equations and antisymmetry of FμνFμν​: ∂μTμν=−αFναJα+αFναJα=0 ∂μ​Tμν=−αFναJα​+αFναJα​=0 ✅ Conservation verified. 4. Force on Test Particle Particle action: S=∫(−m−x˙2+αXμx˙μ)dτS=∫(−m−x˙2​+αXμ​x˙μ)dτ Equations of motion: ddτ(mx˙μ−x˙2)=αFμνx˙ν dτd​(m−x˙2​x˙μ​​)=αFμν​x˙ν In proper time parametrization (x˙2=−1x˙2=−1): md2xμdτ2=αFμνdxνdτ mdτ2d2xμ​=αFμνdτdxν​​So force density: fμ=αFμνuνfμ=αFμνuν​5. Non-relativistic Limit to Newtonian Gravity Static field: Xμ=(Φ,0⃗)Xμ=(Φ,0 ), so F0i=−∂iΦF0i​=−∂i​Φ, Fij=0Fij​=0 Spatial force component: fi=αFi0u0=α(−∂iΦ)(−1)=α∂iΦ fi=αFi0u0​=α(−∂iΦ)(−1)=α∂iΦ Newton's second law: md2xidt2=α∂iΦmdt2d2xi​=α∂iΦ Compare to Newtonian: md2xidt2=−m∂iΦNmdt2d2xi​=−m∂iΦN​Thus: α∂iΦ=−m∂iΦNα∂iΦ=−m∂iΦN​For universal coupling (α=mα=m): Φ=−ΦNΦ=−ΦN​✅ Recovers r⃗¨=−∇ΦNr ¨=−∇ΦN​ in non-relativistic limit.
